         <abstract id="aspace_f64e48386f12ea2f083461cd0792721b">The records consist of the files of Daniel J. Wallace, Jr. as coach, scrapbooks, correspondence, and photographs documenting polo at Yale. Also included is a research paper on the sport by Alexandra Redding, Class of 2002.</abstract>
         <origination label="creator">
            <corpname identifier="dts_9dcdf4e2b6c6ac61989de83546fba1635b82b9de"
                      rules="aacr"
                      source="naf">
               <part>Yale University. Dept. of Athletics</part>
            </corpname>
         </origination>
    
      </did>
      <odd id="aspace_47dfa42e2955930b967aafbb53af1c12">
         <head>General note</head>
         <p>Forms part of Yale Record Group 38-B (YRG 38-B), Records documenting specific sports at Yale.</p>  
      </odd>
      <altformavail id="aspace_d31973e6526e44046e5f4f69c6bc72d5">
         <head>Existence and Location of Copies</head>
         <p>Polo scrapbooks are available on microfilm from Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library, at cost. Order no. HM185. 1984. 1215 frames on 1 reel, 35mm.</p>  
      </altformavail>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_67274ef748181d8c250250c9fef122ee">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>The records were transferred by the Department of Athletics and private donors, 2001-2005.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_73f18a20bfb4e3bb7f1b26e7da65af38">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>Access to the records is partially restricted. See inventory for details..</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <userestrict id="aspace_151ea57f714e9578adf39234ed5f901f">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
         <p>Patrons must use HM FILM 185 instead of the original scrapbooks.</p>  
      </userestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_3caa21c8669abe93e2573898e989c2cd">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Department of Athletics, Yale University, Records Documenting Polo (RU 908), Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <arrangement id="aspace_533292e0b27c4a88ae4ae5ff824ba992">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged by accession.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_9906037777609ccf0436077c1dd0864f">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of the files of Daniel J. Wallace, Jr. as coach, scrapbooks, correspondence, and photographs documenting polo at Yale. Also included is a research paper on the sport by Alexandra Redding, Class of 2002.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
